# Load balancers
Manage flow of traffic in simple terms.

# forward proxy 
protect private network clients from the world
- Clients traffic go to a web facing server which then is tasked with retrieving the request from outside servers.
  - Outside servers only know the proxy server's IP 

# reverse proxy 
protect servers from outside world. 
- E-com: Clients send requests to a server which then routes that request to the private network of servers.
  - Protect from DDOS since web clients wont know the extact IP address of the servers inside the network they can only target the web facing server.

# Port 443 
HTTP secure transfers 
